                        <p> Fortunately for you, applicants wishing to obtain a California real estate broker license face a rather straightforward process. After completing some easy educational requirements with ADHI Schools and the required experience you can hop on over and test to become a California real estate broker!</p>
                        <p> Keep in mind that you'll also need to pay a couple of small fees to the state in order to take the real estate broker exam in California.  It's $95 for the state examination and $300 for a four-year real estate broker license.   </p>  
